job) — Add a NEW job in the `eval` stage that:\\n- Uses image `node:20-bookworm` (Node.js available natively, no install needed)\\n- Sets `needs: [\\\"eval:llm-judge\\\"]` so it runs only after the eval completes and receives its artifacts\\n- Does NOT set `allow_failure: true` (default is false) — so a threshold violation exit code 1 will hard-gate the pipeline\\n- Has `rules` matching `eval:llm-judge` (i.e., `if: '$OPENROUTER_API_KEY'` with `when: on_success`)\\n- Script: `node scripts/eval-threshold-check.js`\\n- The script resolves paths relative to `__dirname`/repo root, so `eval-thresholds.json` and `eval-baseline.json` are read from the checked-out repo, and `backend/build/eval-results/` comes from the `eval:llm-judge` artifacts\\n\\nThis separation means: the LLM call itself can flake without blocking (`allow_failure: true`), but once results exist, threshold violations are enforced (`allow_failure` defaults to `false` on the new job).\\n\\nAdd convenience npm scripts to `package.json`:\\n- `\\\"eval:check\\\": \\\"node scripts/eval-threshold-check.js\\\"`\\n- `\\\"eval:run\\\": \\\"cd backend && ./gradlew evalTest\\\"`\\n\\nScope: Only modify `.gitlab-ci.yml` and `package.json`. Do NOT modify any backend or frontend source files.\",\n  \"requiredChecks\": [\n    \"build\"\n  ]\n}\n\nYou are the first agent to work on this step.\nImplement the changes described above, run checks to verify, and fix any issues before handing off.\nBe thorough — the next agent will review your work and should find it correct.\n\nPrior observations from earlier steps (address if they fall within this step's scope):\n- [MEDIUM] step 1 backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/ai/evidence/LineageQueryService.java, StructuredEvidenceService.java: Untracked files in working directory (from a previous session), not committed to git. These caused pre-existing spotless violations that I fixed via spotlessApply.\n- [MEDIUM] step 1 backend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/ai/controller/AiCont